{{Infobox Union |<!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template:Infobox Union]] for usage. --> |name= ADIH |country= Haiti |affiliation= |members= |full_name= Association des industries d'Haïti |image= |founded= {{Start date and age|1980|dly=df}}<ref name="AAP">{{cite web|url=http://www.aapnetwork.net/aapmembers/ADIH/|title=ADIH|website=AAP|language=English|accessdate=October 24, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161106064728/http://www.aapnetwork.net/aapmembers/ADIH/|archive-date=2016-11-06|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref><ref name="Hall">{{cite book|last1=Hall|first1=Michael|title=Historical Dictionary of Haiti|date=2012|publisher=The Scarecrow Press|location=Lanham, Toronto, Plymouth|isbn=978-0-8108-7810-5|page=25}}</ref> |current= |office= [[Pétion-Ville]] |people= Grégor Avril, executive director;<ref name="Hall" /> Georges B. Sassine, president<ref name="Jeanty" /> |website= {{URL|http://www.adih.ht}} |footnotes= |native_name= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= Merged into |merged_into= }}
The '''Association des industries d'Haïti''' (ADIH), founded in 1980, is an association of around 100 manufacturers in [[Haiti]].<ref name="Hall" /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.adih.ht|title=Association des industries d'Haïti|language=French|accessdate=October 24, 2016}}</ref> It is currently headed by president George B. Sassine. It is best known internationally for its work promoting assembly plants in Haiti.<ref name="Hall" />
== Chronology == In early 1986, during a period of social upheaval, the ADIH called on the government of [[Jean-Claude Duvalier]] to exercise "tolerance and moderation".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ceïbe|first1=Cathy|title=Le 7 février 1986. Les Haïtiens se libèrent de la dictature, pas encore de la dépendance...|url=https://www.humanite.fr/le-7-fevrier-1986-les-haitiens-se-liberent-de-la-dictature-pas-encore-de-la-dependance-597827|website=Humanité|accessdate=November 5, 2016|language=French|date=February 7, 2016}}</ref> In 1989, it began lobbying efforts on the issue of textile quotas for Haiti.<ref name="AAP" /><ref name="Hall" /> After the [[Jean-Bertrand Aristide#1991 coup d'état|1991 coup d'état]] which brought general [[Raoul Cédras]] to power, the association managed escrow accounts for tax collection from foreign corporate entities in Haiti until 1994.<ref name="Hall" /> In 2004, the association stated that they viewed the second overthrow of [[Jean-Bertrand Aristide]] as a positive development.<ref name="Hall" /> In coordination with [[Bill Clinton]],<ref name="KQ_Haiti">{{cite web |last1=Katz |first1=Jonathan |title=The King and Queen of Haiti |url=http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2015/05/clinton-foundation-haiti-117368 |website=Politico |accessdate=September 21, 2016 |date=May 4, 2015}}</ref> they successfully lobbied the US government from 2003 to 2006 to ensure that textiles coming from Haiti would no longer be subject to import tariffs. (Cf. [[Economy of Haiti|HOPE & HELP]])<ref name="Hall" /><ref>{{cite web|author1=Stefan Viard (trans.)|author2=Patrick Saint Pré|author3=Juno Jean Baptiste|title=The ADIH fully supports the renewal of HOPE|url=http://lenouvelliste.com/lenouvelliste/article/139536/The-ADIH-fully-supports-the-renewal-of-HOPE|website=Le Nouvelliste|accessdate=October 24, 2016|language=English|date=December 19, 2014}}</ref> In 2009, they opposed the parliamentary vote to raise the minimum wage in Haiti to 200 gourdes an hour.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Michel|first1=Carlin|title=L'ADIH rejette le salaire minimum|url=http://lenouvelliste.com/lenouvelliste/article/70215/LADIH-rejette-le-salaire-minimum|website=Le Nouvelliste|language=French|accessdate=October 24, 2016|date=May 13, 2009}}</ref> In 2013 the association again lobbied against a minimum wage increase,<ref>{{cite web|last1=ADIH|title=Le cri de l'ADIH|url=http://lenouvelliste.com/lenouvelliste/article/124555/Le-cri-de-lADIH|language=French|website=Le Nouvelliste|accessdate=October 24, 2016|date=November 28, 2013}}</ref> and argued that strikes would damage the Haitian garment industry.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lall|first1=Rashmee Roshan|title=Haiti minimum wage increase ignites competition row in textile industry|url=https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/poverty-matters/2013/dec/31/haiti-minimum-wage-increase-ignites-row-textile-industry|website=The Guardian|accessdate=November 5, 2016|date=December 31, 2013}}</ref> They likewise argued against a minimum wage increase in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Roberson|first1=Alphonse|title=Salaire minimum : le CSS tranche, l’ADIH inconfortable, l’exécutif joue le temps…|url=http://lenouvelliste.com/lenouvelliste/article/158630/Salaire-minimum-le-CSS-tranche-lADIH-inconfortable-lexecutif-joue-le-temps|website=Le Nouvelliste|language=French|accessdate=October 24, 2016|date=May 6, 2016}}</ref>
More recently, the ADIH met with [[Jocelerme Privert]] to discuss the consequences of smuggling.<ref name="Jeanty">{{cite web|last1=Jeanty|first1=Gérard Junior|title=ADIH rencontre Privert et pose les problèmes de la contrebande|url=http://lenouvelliste.com/lenouvelliste/article/161601/ADIH-rencontre-Privert-et-pose-les-problemes-de-la-contrebande|website=Le Nouvelliste|language=French|accessdate=October 24, 2016|date=August 1, 2016}}</ref>
