[[Image:FrieleEdit.jpg|thumb|upright|Herman Friele]]
'''Herman Friele''' (born August 21, 1943) is a Norwegian [[businessman]] and politician for the [[Conservative Party of Norway|Conservative Party]]. He has been [[chairman]] of the coffee manufacturer [[Friele]] since 1981, as the seventh generation Friele in charge of the company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Herman_Friele/utdypning_%E2%80%93_1|work=Store norske leksikon|title=Herman Friele – utdypning – 1 (NBL-artikkel)|first=Norvall|last=Skreien}}</ref> He was the highly popular [[List of mayors of Bergen|mayor]] of [[Bergen]] from 2003 to 2007.<ref name=bt>{{cite news|url=http://www.bt.no/lokalt/bergen/article289782.ece|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130222171836/http://www.bt.no/lokalt/bergen/article289782.ece|dead-url=yes|archive-date=22 February 2013|work=Bergens Tidende|title=Friele trekker seg med et smil|date=16 August 2006|first=Kari|last=Pedersen}}</ref>

Before the [[Norwegian local elections, 2003|2003 election]], a survey found that 64% of the inhabitants of Bergen wanted him to become the [[mayor]] after the election.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bt.no/nyheter/lokalt/To-av-tre-vil-ha-Friele-som-ordfoerer-67256.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120721214829/http://www.bt.no/nyheter/lokalt/To-av-tre-vil-ha-Friele-som-ordfoerer-67256.html |dead-url=yes |archive-date=21 July 2012 |work=Bergens Tidende |title=To av tre vil ha Friele som ordfører |date=11 September 2003 }}</ref> When Friele announced that he would not be running for mayor in the [[Norwegian local elections, 2007|2007 election]],<ref name=bt/> a survey showed that 60% of the inhabitants of Bergen wanted him to continue in the job.{{Citation needed|date=September 2007}}

