'''Leo Geeris''' is a prominent [[Dutch people|Dutch]] [[businessman]] and [[investor]]. He was ranked in the 350 richest persons in the [[Netherlands]], and is especially active in the [[real estate]] sector. Leo Geeris is a sponsor for many charities and sport events.

== Investments ==

Leo Geeris is known for investing in airports,<ref>[http://www.rhein-main.net/sixcms/detail.php/rmn01.c.5671379.de/v2_rmn_news_local_article rhein-main.net]{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> department stores,<ref>[http://www.op-online.de/nachrichten/neu-isenburg/generalunternehmer-saniert-shop-west-338975.html op-online.de]</ref> railways,<ref>[http://www.faz.net/s/Rub8D05117E1AC946F5BB438374CCC294CC/Doc~E484B691EE76E4FE9B47B2A0F7291DA30~ATpl~Ecommon~Scontent.html faz.net]</ref> and restaurants.<ref>[http://www.fr-online.de/frankfurt_und_hessen/nachrichten/kreis_offenbach/1656550_Edles-Ambiente-im-alten-Schuppen.html fr-online.de]{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Among the richest 500 people in the Netherlands in 2009, Geeris declared bankruptcy in September 2011.<ref>[http://www.vastgoedmarkt.nl/nieuws/2011/10/03/Vastgoedondernemer-Leo-Geeris-failliet [Vastgoedondernemer Leo Geeris failliet], 3 October 2011</ref><ref>[http://www.quotenet.nl/biz/voormalig-quote500lid-sleurt-eega-mee-in-faillissement.php Voormalig Quote 500-lid sleurt eega mee in faillissement], Quote 500, 1 May 2012</ref>

