[[File:Lisa Sounio.jpg|thumb|Lisa Sounio]]

'''Lisa Sounio''' (born 1970) is a past CEO and chairperson of social networking site [[Dopplr]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dopplr.com/main/about |title=About Dopplr |accessdate=2010-01-25}}</ref> She is also the CEO of her own design management consultancy [[Sonay]]. She has a background in industrial design management. Early in her career she worked as a sales- and export manager in the Finnish furniture industry. Before becoming an entrepreneur she worked for [[Iittala]] where she was in charge of branding and product design development.

Sounio has a [[masters degree]] from the [[Helsinki School of Economics]]. She has also studied at the [[University of Art and Design Helsinki]] and at the [[Helsinki University of Technology]]. She is also a columnist and public speaker. Sounio is married to and a business partner of [[Marko Ahtisaari]].

She was a candidate for the 2014 [[European Parliament election, 2014 (Finland)|Finnish European Parliament election]], on the [[National Coalition Party]] list, but was not elected.

